The '''Aged and Disability Pensioners Party''' was a minor [[Australia]]n political party that contested the [[Australian federal election, 2004|2004 federal election]]. The party was established on 13 December 2001.<ref name="aec"/> It supported the rights of [[pension]]ers. It was dissolved on 18 January 2006.<ref name="aec">{{cite web|title=The Aged and Disability Pensioners Party|url=http://www.aec.gov.au/parties_and_representatives/party_registration/Deregistered_parties/tadpp.htm|work=Australian Electoral Commission|accessdate=6 May 2016|date=5 January 2011}}</ref>

