'''Her Britannic Majesty''', or '''His Britannic Majesty''' ('''HBM'''),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/hbm|title=HBM definition and meaning - Collins English Dictionary|website=www.collinsdictionary.com}}</ref> depending on the [[gender|sex]] of the [[monarch]], is a formal, or [[official]], term for the [[sovereignty|sovereign]] [[Political power|power]] of the [[United Kingdom]] in [[diplomacy]], the [[law of nation]]s, and [[international relations]].

For example, in the [[Mandatory Palestine|Mandate for Palestine]] of the [[League of Nations]], it was ''His Britannic Majesty'' who was designated as the [[League of Nations mandate|Mandatory]] for [[Palestine (region)|Palestine]].

Britannic Majesty is used in all [[British passport]]s, where the following sentence is used:
<blockquote>
Her Britannic Majesty's Secretary of State Requests and requires in the Name of Her Majesty all those whom it may concern to allow the bearer to pass freely without let or hindrance, and to afford the bearer such assistance and protection as may be necessary.
</blockquote>

This is a reduced version of the wording on this British passport, issued in 1979:
<blockquote>
Her Britannic Majesty's Principal [[Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs]] Requests and requires in the Name of Her Majesty all those whom it may concern to allow the bearer to pass freely without let or hindrance, and to afford the bearer such assistance and protection as may be necessary.
</blockquote>

