[[File:Arvin, Kern County, California. ... Close-up of relief queue on S.R.A. pay day. Man in foreground is . . . - NARA - 521652.jpg|thumb|Close-up of relief queue on S.R.A. pay day, [[Arvin, California|Arvin]], CA, 1940]]
The '''California State Relief Administration (SRA)''', created in 1935, was the successor to the '''State Emergency Relief Administration (SERA)''', created in 1933. The agencies were responsible for distributing state and federal funds to improve conditions in California during the [[Great Depression in the United States|Great Depression]], and administered [[unemployment benefits|unemployment relief]].<ref>{{Cite web | title = Inventory of the State Relief Administration Records | accessdate = 2012-03-01 | url = http://www.oac.cdlib.org/findaid/ark:/13030/tf4489n6b0/ }}</ref>
