'''Corruption in Albania''' is a problem.<ref>[http://www.transparency.org/policy_research/surveys_indices/cpi 2012 Corruption Perceptions Index] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060619145956/http://www.transparency.org/policy_research/surveys_indices/cpi |date=2006-06-19 }}, [[Transparency International]]</ref> According to [[Global Corruption Barometer]] 2013, 66% of respondents indicated that level of corruption has increased in Albania.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.transparency.org/gcb2013/country/?country=albania|title=Albania 2013 - World's largest opinion survey on corruption - Transparency International|last=e.V.|first=Transparency International|website=www.transparency.org|access-date=2017-06-22}}</ref>

Transparency International's 2017 Corruption Perception Index ranks the country 91st place out of 180 countries with score 38. (39 in 2016, 36 in 2015, 33 in 2014 and 31 in 2013).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.transparency.org/news/feature/corruption_perceptions_index_2017|title=Corruption Perceptions Index 2017|last=e.V.|first=Transparency International|date=|work=www.transparency.org|access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref>

Corruption is still considered one of the most problematic factors for establishing business in Albania.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Business Corruption in Albania|url=http://www.business-anti-corruption.com/country-profiles/europe-central-asia/albania/show-all.aspx|publisher=Business Anti-Corruption Portal|accessdate= 14 July 2015}}</ref>  Even though anti-corruption legal framework of Albania is moderate, its enforcement is weak and corruption conviction rates are still very low.<ref name=":0" />

