{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Economy |nativename = ''Ekonomi Bakanlığı'' |logo = |logo_caption = |seal = Ministry of Economy (Turkey).png |seal_width = 150px |seal_caption = |picture = T.C. Ekonomi Bakanlığı.jpg |picture_width = 200px |picture_caption = Headquarters of Ministry of Economy in Ankara, Turkey. |headquarters = [[Ankara]] |formed = 29 June 2011 |preceding = Dış Ticaret Müsteşarlığı |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Government of Turkey]] |employees = |budget = 1.454.494.000 TL (2014) |minister1_name = [[Nihat Zeybekçi]] |minister1_pfo = Minister of the Economy |chief1_name = Fatih Metin |chief1_position = {{small|Deputy Minister}} |chief2_name = İbrahim Şenel |chief2_position = {{small|Undersecretary}} |chief3_name = [[Kadir Bal]] |chief3_position = {{small|Deputy Undersecretary}} |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = {{url|http://www.ekonomi.gov.tr/}} |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Economy''' ({{lang-tr|Ekonomi Bakanlığı}}) is a government department responsible for the [[Economy of Turkey|economic affairs]] of the [[Republic of Turkey]]. It was established following the [[Turkish general election, 2011|2011 general election]] with [[Justice and Development Party (Turkey)|Justice and Development Party]] (AKP) Member of Parliament [[Zafer Çağlayan]] being appointed as the first Minister of the Economy. The current minister, undersecretary, and deputy undersecretaries are [[Nihat Zeybekçi]], [[İbrahim Şenel]] and [[Kadir Bal]], respectively, .<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekonomi.gov.tr/index.cfm?sayfa=bakanlikofisi&bolum=ozgecmis |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-02-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140204153228/http://www.ekonomi.gov.tr/index.cfm?sayfa=bakanlikofisi&bolum=ozgecmis |archivedate=2014-02-04 |df= }}</ref>
