'''Trudoden''' ({{lang-ru|Трудодень}}) was a unit of value and type of accounting of quantity and quality of labor (as a [[factors of production|factor of production]]) in collective farms ([[kolkhoz]]es) of the [[Soviet Union]] in 1930 – 1966. It literally means a day of labor. It also was a form of wage payments.<ref name=melnyczuk/>
Members of collective farms were paid based on the amount of trudodni (plural form) earned.<ref>Nove, A. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=S98ABAAAQBAJ&pg=PA191&lpg=PA191&dq=trudoden&source=bl&ots=hUrqEixpfg&sig=_P1P8SpDcKgqTQXCkZPo-GA6kN8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_r4PT_YbcAhUH5YMKHZn9Br0Q6AEIWjAL#v=onepage&q=trudoden&f=false Was Stalin Really Necessary?: Some Problems of Soviet Economic Policy]''. Routledge, 2014. {{ISBN|9781136629488}}</ref><ref>Boterbloem, K. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=XwoINDqBbOsC&pg=PA239&lpg=PA239&dq=trudoden&source=bl&ots=wvGe69Bdfz&sig=uyCAMObdopbWkFnpnLl35G6Nz_Y&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_r4PT_YbcAhUH5YMKHZn9Br0Q6AEIYDAN#v=onepage&q=trudoden&f=false Life and Death under Stalin: Kalinin Province, 1945-1953]''. McGill-Queen's Press - MQUP, 1999. {{ISBN|9780773567597}}</ref><ref>Jeffries, I. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=COtkAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA155&lpg=PA155&dq=trudoden&source=bl&ots=Qk_UuUSF6B&sig=p7VkLjdpTI2tRrxWChXzStD3H7U&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwio3pWUjIfcAhUk5IMKHRV7BH44FBDoAQgxMAI#v=onepage&q=trudoden&f=false The New Russia: A Handbook of Economic and Political Developments]''. Routledge, 2013. {{ISBN|9781136870651}}</ref> Payments to the collective farm members were made with natural products such as grain when and if they were able to realize their products.<ref name=melnyczuk>Melnyczuk, L. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=CufBAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA57&lpg=PA57&dq=trudoden&source=bl&ots=ug3TY0LG06&sig=humD5hbzrbuie8sJZe0A7VzHgx8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi_r4PT_YbcAhUH5YMKHZn9Br0Q6AEIXTAM#v=onepage&q=trudoden&f=false Silent Memories, Traumatic Lives]''. Western Australian Museum, 2012. {{ISBN|9781925040029}}</ref>
